  E'BIRTH YEAR: 1941 (year precision)\nSource: velhosmestres.com explicitly states "1941"\n\nDEATH DATE: December 26, 1970 (exact precision)\nSource: velhosmestres.com explicitly states "26 Dec 1970"\n\nNAME VARIATIONS:\n- "Cutica" - primary apelido\n- "Índio" - alternate apelido\n- "Nelson Moraes Paes" - full name\n\nFAMILY:\n- Brother: Nilton Moraes Paes (Oct 16, 1937 - before 1979)\n- Brother: Fernando Olímpio Paes Filho (Fernandinho/Mano) (Mar 26, 1948 - May 5, 2001)\n- Sister: Norma Moraes Paes (research informant for velhosmestres.com)\n- Total of 19 siblings (14 boys, 5 girls)\n\nTEACHERS:\n- Ninho from Ribeira (first teacher, via rodas at Argolo Square)\n- Mestre Pierrô (student of Zeca do Uruguai)\n- Mestre Zeca do Uruguai (elder master in Uruguai neighborhood)\n\nSTUDENTS:\n- Mestre Nô (Norival Moreira de Oliveira, born June 22, 1945) - awarded diploma jointly with Nilton on Sept 18, 1964\n\nMEDIA APPEARANCES:\n- 1979: Tribute at Academia de Capoeira Angola Orixás da Bahia party (posthumous)\n\nRODA LOCATIONS:\n- Argolo Square (between Massaranduba and Jardim Cruzeiro)\n- Uruguai neighborhood (with Zeca and Pierrô)',
